The patient's symptoms of progressive weakness in legs and arms, worsening day by day, are highly classic for Guillain-Barré Syndrome (GBS), an acute inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy. In summary, while the patient's symptoms strongly point towards Guillain-Barré Syndrome, the proposed diagnostic workup by the doctor is largely inadequate and includes several irrelevant tests.
